# gen59 (C5): best-effort over the blank wall. "what is <X>?" reuses the KB
# description path instead of falling back when X is known.
> Socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> Socrates is a mortal
< Learned: mortal(socrates).
> what is Socrates?
< socrates is a man; socrates is a mortal.
> what is a_flamingo?
< I don't know anything about a_flamingo.

# gen146 (E5): open-domain humility. These are not answered from general
# knowledge; parrot0 names the exact missing relation/predicate/tool and offers
# a useful next action.
> what is the capital of france?
< I do not know the relation capital yet, so I cannot answer the capital of france. You can teach me with thing is the capital of france, or give facts/rules to reason from.
> why is the sky blue?
< I do not know why sky is blue: I have no blue(sky) fact/rule or cause explaining it. Teach me facts or rules, or give me a passage to read.
> what year is it?
< I do not know the current year: I have no current_year fact or clock/calendar tool. Tell me the year, or give facts I can reason from.

# 10x stress: held-out relation/predicate/current-tool gaps. The response must
# stay scoped to the missing support, never pretend to know the world fact.
